---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import { SITE, SOCIAL } from "@/lib/constants";

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`Learn more about ${SITE.author} and the blog blog.labjp.xyz`}
  lang={lang}
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 lg:py-16">

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">
      About <em class="not-italic text-primary">blog.labjp.xyz</em>
    </h1>

    <!-- About the publication -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-4 mb-12">
      <p>
        <em class="text-primary">blog.labjp.xyz</em> documents how cloud native architecture evolves in enterprise environments.
      </p>

      <p>
        It's not a news feed or a framework showcase.
        It's a growing map of patterns that help large systems evolve without breaking.
      </p>

      <p>The focus is on:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>Kubernetes and OpenShift for enterprise environments</li>
        <li>Cloud native architectures and pragmatic design decisions</li>
        <li>AI systems integrated with Java</li>
        <li>Developer experience as a design constraint</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        I write for people who design systems that must survive real production pressure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- About Me -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">About Me</h3>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-4 mb-12">
      <p>
        I'm Jean Paul Lopez.
        Senior Consultant at Red Hat with over 8 years in enterprise software.
      </p>

      <p>
        I help companies adopt Kubernetes, OpenShift, and cloud native architectures.
        Everything I share here is in a personal capacity.
      </p>

      <p>
        This blog is not an opinion outlet.
        It's my working notebook for modern architecture.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- What You Will Find -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">What You'll Find</h3>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-4 mb-12">
      <p>You won't find content that chases trends.</p>

      <p>You'll find:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>Architecture patterns that scale beyond tutorials</li>
        <li>Practical guides for modernizing large Java systems</li>
        <li>Deep dives into Kubernetes, OpenShift, GitOps, and AI</li>
        <li>Real trade-off analysis in platforms</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Each article is connected to others through shared concepts and patterns.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Why Subscribe -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Why Subscribe</h3>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-4 mb-12">
      <p>Because code alone doesn't modernize systems.</p>

      <p>Subscribers get:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>Writing focused on what truly matters in enterprise architecture</li>
        <li>Access to the complete archive of tutorials and essays</li>
        <li>A steady stream of architectural thinking, not weekly noise</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="font-semibold">
        Write boring code. Deploy exciting systems.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Stay Connected -->
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Connect</h3>

    <ul class="space-y-3 text-base">
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub:</strong>{" "}
        <a href={SOCIAL.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">
          @jeanlopezxyz
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>LinkedIn:</strong>{" "}
        <a href={SOCIAL.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">
          @jeanlopezxyz
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>X:</strong>{" "}
        <a href={SOCIAL.twitter} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">
          @jeanlopezxyz
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>RSS:</strong>{" "}
        <a href="/rss.xml" class="text-primary hover:underline">
          blog.labjp.xyz/rss.xml
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
